kingdom of King Yudhishthir.

169
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:12,800
Yes, that's right.

170
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:21,810
Bring that along as well.
That would be useful.

171
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:23,970
Our King Yudhishthir never lies

172
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,940
and we wish to stand
by a truthful person.

173
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,770
So many people

174
00:20:46,930 --> 00:20:49,700
are migrating to
Indraprastha, uncle?!

175
00:20:49,830 --> 00:20:52,780
It is human nature,
my darling.

176
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:55,880
He hopes to find new joy

177
00:20:55,930 --> 00:20:58,840
in the new objects he finds.

178
00:21:02,660 --> 00:21:03,830
The water of the ocean

179
00:21:04,730 --> 00:21:07,710
wishes to touch the sky
in the form of waves.

180
00:21:07,860 --> 00:21:09,740
The water in the sky

181
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:12,740
desires to fall as rain
on the mountains.

182
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:14,870
And when rain falls
on the mountains

183
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,840
it rushes to meet the ocean.

184
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:19,830
When the Pandavas

185
00:21:20,730 --> 00:21:22,710
were leaving with a few
of our subjects, uncle

186
00:21:22,730 --> 00:21:25,710
you had said to let them go.

187
00:21:29,630 --> 00:21:31,730
But now, Hastinapur
will become empty!

188
00:21:33,630 --> 00:21:34,660
